        "last_activity_date": 1394235106,
        "creation_date": 1394232405,
        "body": "<p>You might use <a href=\"http://docs.spring.io/spring/docs/3.2.7.RELEASE/javadoc-api/org/springframework/jdbc/core/namedparam/NamedParameterJdbcTemplate.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">NamedParameterJdbcTemplate<\/a> which supports named parameter binding (using <code>:foo<\/code> instead of <code>?<\/code>) and collection parameter expansion (expanding <code>:foo<\/code> to <code>?, ?, ?<\/code>). Then you can use:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>jdbcTemplate.queryForObject(\"SELECT * FROM stored_procedure({:notes})\", \n    Collections.singletonMap(\"notes\", notes));\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>I don't think PostgreSQL JDBC driver supports array parameter types (i.e. you can not bind array to a single <code>?<\/code>).<\/p>\n",
